Nigeria Suspends Chief Justice, Appeal Court Head, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-03-10T08:51:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/nigeria-suspends-chief-justice-appeal-court-head-thisday-says.html
Nigeria suspended its chief
justice, Alosyius Katsina-Alu, and the president of the appeal
court, Ayo Salami, pending an investigation of misconduct,
 ThisDay  reported, citing the National Judicial Council.  A five-member panel will investigate allegations against
the two justices, according to the Lagos-based newspaper. The
group has three months to complete investigations, ThisDay said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at   dmbachu@bloomberg.net . 